jcabi Maven Skin

  Use it in your <<<site.xml>>>, as explained in
  {{{http://maven.apache.org/plugins/maven-site-plugin/examples/sitedescriptor.html#Skinning}skinning}}:

+--
<project>
  [...]
  <skin>
    <groupId>com.jcabi</groupId>
    <artifactId>jcabi-maven-skin</artifactId>
    <version>${project.version}</version>
  </skin>
  [...]
</project>
+--

  This site is using <<<jcabi-maven-skin>>>.
